message.entry: This function only supports real inputs.
Matrix dimensions must agree.
Dimension argument must be a positive integer scalar within indexing range.
Function is not defined for half inputs.
Use of half-precision data type requires Fixed-Point Designer or MATLAB Coder to be installed.
Imaginary part is ignored.
Incorrect dimensions for matrix multiplication. Check that the number of columns in the first matrix matches the number of rows in the second matrix. To perform elementwise multiplication, use '.*'.
Expected input {0} to be a scalar.

Arguments must be 2-D, or at least one argument must be scalar. Use TIMES (.*) for elementwise multiplication, use PAGEMTIMES to apply matrix multiplication to the pages of N-D arrays, or use TENSORPROD to find a product between two N-D arrays.
Input for imaginary part must be a real, full numeric value.
Value must be numeric or logical.
Input for real part must be a real, full numeric value.
Imaginary part of complex argument is ignored.
Colon operands must be all the same type, or mixed with real scalar doubles.
Complex values cannot be converted to logicals.
NaN values cannot be converted to logicals.
Colon operands must be real scalars.
Colon operands must be in the range of the data type.
Invalid data type.
Input arguments must not be sparse.
Fixed point value cannot be cast to half.
bfloat16 is currently an unsupported data type.
Elements of a dimension vector must be unique.
